uch organizations as the ACLU and LULAC in the fight to improve educational and political opportunities for Mexican Americans. Yet his fervor was not always appreciated by those for whom he advocated, and some of his more unpopular stands made him a polarizing figure within the Latino community.Carlos Blanton has published the first biography of this complex man of notable contradictions. The author honors Sánchez's efforts, hitherto mostly unrecognized, in the struggle for equal opportunity, while not shying away from his subject's personal faults and foibles. The result is a long-overdue portrait of a towering figure in mid-twentieth-century America and the all-important cause to which he dedicated his life: Mexican American integration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aEducation, BilingualzSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducatorszTexasvBiography. 0aIntellectualszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aMexican AmericansvBiography. 0aMexican AmericansxCivil rightszSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican AmericansxSegregationzSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aPolitical activistszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSocial reformerszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Cultural Heritage.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300210422.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  a